                <p>Culture is an intangible yet integral part of the identity of an individual forming the foundation on which their life and heritage are shaped making it a fascinating aspect for exploration and prompting travellers to undertake<b> cultural tourism</b> which allows them to better understand and connect with the world and the vast variety of people around them. </p><p>
                    </p><h2>Best Cultural Spots around the world</h2>
                <p>The top 6 locations around the world one from each of the six continents of the planet that travellers must visit to learn about <b>global culture</b> are included in the detailed list below to help travellers: </p>

                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Melbourne: </b>The first on this list is Melbourne city of the Victoria state of Australia which is one of the most well-known cities of the continent known both for its scenic location on the shores of Port Phillip Bay as well as the beautiful structures lining the city forming a beautiful blend of the old and the new. </p>
                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Mexico City: </b>Mexico City of the country of Mexico is arguably the most popular destination among tourists looking to get a taste of the culture of South America and is home to remnants of both the fascinating Aztec empire and buildings from Spanish Colonial times. </p>
                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Pisa: </b>The city of Pisa in the Tuscany region of Italy in Europe is well known all over the world for the architectural wonder of the Leaning Tower of Pisa but also has many other historical locations such as churches, bridges, palaces and castles as well as artefacts in museums. </p>
                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Cape Town: </b>Cape Town of the Western Cape province of South Africa of the African continent is a famous destination of the continent known to travellers for the rich history of resistance and progress it holds through the intricate blending of traditional and colonial architecture. </p>
                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Montreal: </b>Montreal is a part of the Quebec province of Canada country of the continent of North America and is known for being home to the fantastic festivals held every year and the beautiful buildings from the French colonial period in the Gothic style of architecture. </p>
                <p><b><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-point-right"></i> Tokyo: </b>Tokyo is a city in the Kantō region of the Honshu Island of Japan country of the Asian continent and is a unique junction of both traditional and modern urban architecture such as shrines, palaces and skyscrapers.</p>
                <h3>Nearest Airport to the locations</h3>
                <p>The nearest airport to the destinations which are most important to the<b> tourism </b>of the city described above are given in the list below: </p>
